  "text": "For epithelial cell cultures, cornea or conjunctiva explants were extracted from female C57BL/6J or TLR4KO mice. Conjunctiva explants were cultured using methods similar to those described previously. [CITATION_1] Conjunctiva explants were excised from the forniceal conjunctiva of 6-to 8-week-old female C57BL/6 mice or TLR4KO mice and left for 15 minutes at 378C in keratinocyte serum-free medium (KSFM) (Thermo Fisher Scientific) supplemented with 3% fetal bovine serum, 1.25 lg/mL amphotericin B (product 15290-018; Thermo Fisher Scientific), 0.5 lL/mL gentamicin (product 15750-060; Thermo Fisher Scientific), and 5 lg/mL dispase II (product 04942078001; Roche). For cornea cultures, explants were left for 30 minutes in supplemented hormone epithelium medium (SHEM) containing Dulbecco modified Eagle medium/F12 medium (product D8437; Sigma-Aldrich Corp.) supplemented with 5 ng/mL epidermal growth factor (EGF), 5 lg/mL insulin, 5 lg/mL transferrin, 5 ng/mL sodium selenite, 0.5 lg/mL hydrocortisone, 30 ng/mL cholera toxin A, 0.5% dimethyl sulfoxide, 50 lg/mL gentamicin, 1.25 lg/mL amphotericin B, 5% fetal bovine serum, and 5 lg/mL dispase II (Roche). Corneal and conjunctival explants were then plated at one explant per well in 24-well plates. Conjunctiva cultures received 500 lL/ well of KSFM with 80 ng/mL mouse EGF (BD Biosciences, San Jose, CA, USA) and cornea cultures received 500 lL/well SHEM. Culture plates were then placed in a 378C incubator with 5% CO 2 . After 3 days, cornea cultures received 500 lL of fresh SHEM/well for a total of 1 mL medium/well; medium was changed every 3 days. For conjunctiva cultures, wells received another 500 lL of KSFM on day 7 for a total of 1 mL of medium/well. On day 11, wells were left untreated or treated with 1 lL of 1 lg/lL LPS dissolved in endotoxin-free water.",
